
==Setup Your Repository==

The main foursquared repo is at http://joelapenna.com/git/foursquared.git

*Some files must be manually created in order for the tests and source to build.*

*Create main/res/values/credentials.xml* -- do not check this in. It must contain strings:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<resources>
  <string
    name="google_maps_api_key">SOME_TEST_KEY</string>

  <string
    name="oauth_consumer_key">SOME_OTHER_KEY</string>
  <string
    name="oauth_consumer_secret">SOME_OTHER_OTHER_KEY</string>


  <!-- A stanza like this will be sufficient if you're not testing dumpcatcher capabilities. ->
  <string
    name="dumpcatcher_url"></string>
  <string
    name="dumpcatcher_product_key"></string>
  <string
    name="dumpcatcher_secret"></string>

  <!-- A stanza like this will be sufficient if you're not testing dumpcatcher capabilities. ->
  <string
    name="test_dumpcatcher_url"></string>
  <string
    name="test_dumpcatcher_product_key"></string>
  <string
    name="test_dumpcatcher_secret"></string>


</resources>

*Create tests/src/com/joelapenna/foursquare/TestConstants.java* -- do not check this in. It must contain strings:

public class TestConstants {

    static final String oAuthConsumerKey = "SOME_OTHER_KEY";
    static final String oAuthConsumerSecret = "SOME_OTHER_OTHER_KEY";

    static final String testFoursquareUsername = "testuser@example.com";
    static final String testFoursquarePassword = "some_password";

	public static final String testFoursquarePhone = "";
	public static final String testFoursquarePassword = "";

}


==Setting up Eclipse==

Create 2 android projects, one rooted at $foursquared_repo/main/ the other at
$foursquared_repo/tests. Name the former "foursquared" and the latter
"foursquared_tests."

As long as they are named like this, the provided .project files should work.



